commit.message:
Add missing extern qualifiers in ircterm.h

This fixes compiling with -fno-common, which is now the default on new versions of gcc and clang.
(See https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=85678)
Do not try to parse URL from a NULL line. Fixes #20.
Fixes files over 2GB in size reported with negative size.
Fix FiSH messages being cut off when padding is enabled.
Make URL catcher work with encrypted messages (strip non-visible characters used for padding).
Added support for desktop notifications.
Prevent more crashes when server does not exist.
Prepare a new release.
If SSL data is available consume it immediately without relying on select.
Report connection failure in standard way when certificate checks fail. When certificate verification is disabled, print messages anyway to inform user about certificate status.
Add ability to set custom URL buffer size instead of hardcoded limit of 10 URLs.
Fix crash in SETAWAY when current window is not connected to a server.
Reformat for better legibility.
Make sure we don't access server array past array boundaries.
Report if client was built with IPv6 support.
Fix build without colour support.
Added colour setting for URLs (used in public and private messages).
Properly set initial colour attribute for MISC to avoid colours overflowing from other areas.
Simplify saving by reusing setting names from array - also fixes saving of MISC setting.
